---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy. Mykhaylo Kolesnik."
  description="Privacy policy for kolesnik.io. What data is collected, how it is used, and how to request access or deletion."
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <p class="text-sm text-ink-faint mb-3">
      <a href="/">Back to home</a>
    </p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-8 leading-tight">Privacy</h1>

    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
      This page explains what data this website collects, why, and how to exercise your rights
      under the GDPR. The site is operated by Mykhaylo Kolesnik, a sole trader registered in
      Portugal under NIF PT321777301.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl mt-10 mb-4">What this site collects</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
      This site is a static informational page. It does not run analytics, tracking pixels,
      cookies, or third-party advertising scripts. There are no contact forms, comment systems, or
      newsletter signups on this site. The only data captured is the standard server access log
      maintained by the hosting provider for security and reliability purposes (request URL, time,
      IP address, user agent). Those logs are retained on the provider side and used only to
      detect abuse or diagnose outages.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl mt-10 mb-4">Booking and email</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
      The intro-call booking link points to a third-party scheduler (Calendly). When you book a
      call there, Calendly collects the data you provide and is the data controller for that
      interaction. Their privacy policy applies. If you contact me directly by email at
      misha@kolesnik.io, that email is processed by my email provider for the purpose of replying
      to your inquiry. The lawful basis is legitimate interest in handling your request.
      Correspondence is retained for as long as needed to handle the engagement, then archived or
      deleted on request.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl mt-10 mb-4">Your rights</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
      Under the GDPR you have the right to access the data I hold about you, request correction
      or deletion, restrict or object to processing, and lodge a complaint with the Portuguese
      data-protection authority (CNPD). To exercise any of these rights, email
      misha@kolesnik.io and identify the data you would like reviewed. I respond within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl mt-10 mb-4">Engagements</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
      During paid engagements I sign client-provided data-processing agreements or can provide a
      baseline GDPR-aligned DPA on request. Client data accessed during an engagement is treated
      under the terms of that agreement, not this page.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-display text-xl mt-10 mb-4">Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5">
      If this policy changes, the updated text replaces this page. Significant changes (new
      processors, new data categories) will be announced on the home page for at least 30 days.
    </p>

    <p class="text-sm text-ink-faint mt-10">Last updated: 2026-05-06.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
